<REFENTRY id="df">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
df
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>df</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
report filesystem disk space usage
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>df</COMMAND> is as specified in the Single UNIX Specification
but with the
following differences.
</PARA>

<PARA>
If the -k option is not specified, disk space is shown in unspecified
units.  Applications should specify -k.
</PARA>

<PARA>
If  an argument is the absolute file name of a disk device
node containing a mounted filesystem, df shows  the  space
available on that filesystem rather than on the filesystem
containing the device  node  (which  is  always  the  root
filesystem).
</PARA>

</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
